.TH ASCIIZER 1 "March 2026" "version 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
asciizer \- convert images to ASCII art
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B asciizer
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.I image_file
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B asciizer
converts images to ASCII art. It supports JPEG, PNG, and GIF formats with
automatic format detection. Output can be written to a file or printed to
stdout, optionally with ANSI 256-color escape sequences.
.PP
Images are resized to fit the target width (default 80 characters) with
aspect ratio correction for terminal display. Character selection is based
on pixel luminance mapped to a configurable character ramp.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-w " \fIN\fR"
Output width in characters. Default is 80. Set to 0 to disable resizing
and use the original image dimensions.
.TP
.BR \-o " \fIPATH\fR"
Output file path. Default is the input filename with its extension
replaced by \fB.asc\fR.
.TP
.BR \-stdout
Print ASCII art to stdout instead of writing to a file.
.TP
.BR \-invert
Reverse the brightness mapping so that dark pixels use dense characters
and bright pixels use sparse characters.
.TP
.BR \-color
Enable ANSI 256-color output using the 6x6x6 color cube. Character
selection is still based on grayscale luminance for structural detail.
.TP
.BR \-full\-ramp
Use a 70-character gradient ramp instead of the default 10-character
short ramp. Provides finer tonal detail at the cost of less obvious
character shapes.
.TP
.BR \-version
Print version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-completion " \fISHELL\fR"
Print shell completion script to stdout and exit. Supported shells:
\fBzsh\fR, \fBbash\fR.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B asciizer photo.jpg
Convert photo.jpg to ASCII art and save as photo.asc.
.TP
.B asciizer \-stdout photo.png
Print ASCII art to the terminal.
.TP
.B asciizer \-stdout \-color \-w 120 photo.png
Print 120-column color ASCII art to the terminal.
.TP
.B asciizer \-stdout \-invert \-full\-ramp photo.gif
Print inverted ASCII art using the detailed 70-character ramp.
.TP
.B asciizer \-o art.txt \-w 0 photo.jpg
Save at original resolution to art.txt.
.SH SUPPORTED FORMATS
JPEG, PNG, and GIF images are supported. Format is detected automatically
from file contents, not the file extension.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
An error occurred (invalid arguments, unreadable file, unsupported format).
